    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "This lump of coal is always warm to the touch and glows faintly red from within, as if holding an ember of flame waiting to be stoked. No amount of water or coldness can extinguish the coal's warmth. When you hold an *everburning coal* in your hand, you gain resistance 10 to cold and are protected from mild, severe, and extreme cold.  \n   \n In addition, an *everburning coal* is a planar key for *interplanar teleport* and similar magic to travel to the Plane of Fire. When using it this way, you can attune it to the fires of your destination to make it more likely to arrive where you intend to be, appearing 1d6 \u00d7 25 miles from your intended destination instead of 1d10 \u00d7 25 miles away.",
        "level": 12,
        "image": {
            "type": "image",
            "name": "Everburning Coal",
            "image": "EverburningCoal.png"
        },
